snippet: The 20-year-old woman, who is survived by her husband and a 3-year-old child, set fire to herself to protest Chinese rule, according to Western news organizations.
abstract: Young Tibetan mother kills herself by self-immolation to protest Chinese rule; at least 116 Tibetans in Chinese-ruled regions have set fire to themselves since 2009 in acts of protest.
lead_paragraph: The 20-year-old woman, who is survived by her husband and a 3-year-old child, set fire to herself to protest Chinese rule, according to Western news organizations.
